BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..name: Amanda Holliday
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..description: Shipwright to the Tower, Amanda Holliday runs the Hangar like a finely tuned engine.

interactions.flavorLineOne: You blink and Amanda has already swapped her old bandana for one of the new ones you think.
Amanda Holliday was able to recover and repair Cayde's personal jumpship after he fell. She feels that he would have wanted you to have it now.
Amanda is not convinced that this story is over, but she wishes to thank you all the same.
Amanda forgets to wipe the grease off her hands before she accepts the cookies. Oh well.
Amanda congratulates you on your victory! She hopes that when you wield the Chaperone, you remember the humans who made the dangerous journey to the Last Safe City.
"It's been a long year," Amanda says with a weary smile. "And we've lost a lot." She claps a hand on your shoulder. "Let's celebrate what we still have, right?"

headerDisplayProperties.description: Cayde-6 and Amanda Holliday were close. Go check on her to see how she's processing Cayde's death.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Amanda Holliday

interactions.flavorLineOne: Amanda is resilient. If she weren't, she would never have made it to the Last City. But losing your family never gets easier.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Amanda will be glad to get closure and to see you safe. Go talk to her in the Tower Hangar.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Amanda Holliday

interactions.flavorLineOne: Amanda has a tale to tell: one of a death gone unnoticed and a wrong to be righted.
Amanda congratulates you on defeating the Nightmare in the Haunted Forest and encourages you to return for more holiday cheer.
The Tex Mechanica weapons foundry has declared a Crucible contest. The prize is a weapon based on the Chaperone, a shotgun Nora Holliday used to protect her family on the refugee roads to the City.
Amanda reflects on how the Festival of the Lost feels this year, and she gives you a gift to celebrate.
With help from an old friend, Amanda has figured out the cause of the weirdness on Io.

Amanda Holliday is back in the Hangar and doing what she loves mosttinkering with and rebuilding ships and Sparrows. She might not be a Guardian, but she certainly left her mark on the Red War.

Visit Amanda for all your ship and Sparrow needs.
Amanda has caught a break in the hunt for clues about Master Ives.

"If you wanna know how some of the greatest battles in Guardian history were fought, I've lived through some of the recent ones. Now listen close"

You can replay classic campaigns by acquiring the quests here. You can play each campaign only once per character.

After acquiring the quest, track it to see where to go to play the next mission.
